---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---
<Base title="About" description="About NoviForge — enterprise IT expertise in IBM software, infrastructure, and high availability.">
  <section class="hero" style="padding: 3.5rem 1.5rem;">
    <h1>About NoviForge</h1>
    <p>Enterprise IT consulting rooted in decades of hands-on experience.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="section" style="max-width: 820px;">
    <h2 class="section-title">Background</h2>
    <p>
      NoviForge was founded by Jaco Wisse, a senior IT architect and consultant with extensive
      experience in enterprise software, infrastructure engineering, and platform design.
      Over the years, the focus has been on delivering robust, production-grade solutions
      for organisations that demand the highest standards of reliability and security.
    </p>

    <h2 class="section-title" style="margin-top: 2.5rem;">IBM Software Expertise</h2>
    <p>
      A significant part of our background lies in the IBM software ecosystem. We have hands-on
      experience with IBM WebSphere Application Server, IBM MQ (message queuing), IBM API Connect,
      and IBM DataPower Gateway. This foundation gives us a deep understanding of enterprise
      integration patterns, high-throughput messaging, and API governance at scale.
    </p>

    <h2 class="section-title" style="margin-top: 2.5rem;">Development</h2>
    <p>
      From monolithic Java EE applications to cloud-native microservices, we have designed and
      built software across the full spectrum. Our development philosophy emphasises clean
      architecture, automated testing, CI/CD pipelines, and Infrastructure as Code — ensuring
      that what we build is maintainable and evolvable over time.
    </p>

    <h2 class="section-title" style="margin-top: 2.5rem;">Infrastructure</h2>
    <p>
      We design and operate infrastructure for demanding workloads: bare-metal Linux systems,
      virtualised environments (KVM, VMware), and container platforms (Kubernetes, OpenShift).
      Automation is central to everything we do — Ansible, Terraform, and GitOps workflows
      reduce toil and eliminate configuration drift.
    </p>

    <h2 class="section-title" style="margin-top: 2.5rem;">High Availability &amp; Disaster Recovery</h2>
    <p>
      Business continuity requires systems that stay up. We architect high-availability solutions
      using active/passive and active/active clustering, load balancing, and health-check-driven
      failover. Disaster recovery planning, RTO/RPO analysis, and runbook development are part
      of our standard engagement toolkit — so that when things go wrong, recovery is fast,
      tested, and predictable.
    </p>
  </section>
</Base>
